<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC, EURATOM, ECSC) No 1180/92 of 30 April 1992 fixing a weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants of the European Communities serving in Munich </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 1180/92, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes kohaldatav paranduskoefitsient 30. aprill 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing a Single Council and a Single Commission of the European Communities, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;htse n&otilde;ukogu ja &uuml;htse komisjoni asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of officials and the conditions of employment of other servants of the European Communities laid down by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 571/92 (2), and in particular Article 64 of the Staff Regulations and Article 9 of Annex XI thereto and the first paragraph of Article 20 and Article 64 of the Conditions of Employment, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 571/92, (2) eriti k&otilde;nealuste personalieeskirjade artiklit 64, nende XI lisa artiklit 9 ning teenistustingimuste artikli 20 esimest l&otilde;iku ja artiklit 64, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Statistical Office of the European Communities has conducted surveys to measure the level of the cost of living in certain places of employment in Germany; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Statistikaamet on teinud uuringuid, et m&otilde;&otilde;ta elukalliduse taset teatavates t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohtades Saksamaal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in its Judgment of 23 January 1992 in Case C-301/90, Commission v. Council, the Court of Justice held that: </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Kohus leidis 23. jaanuari 1992. aasta otsuses kohtuasjas C-301/90: komisjon v. n&otilde;ukogu, et: </eesti>
<inglise> ' ... </inglise>
<eesti> &ldquo;... </eesti>
<inglise> At the end of 1987 the cost of living in Munich was 8,3 % higher than in Bonn - the capital at that time - and that, in the absence of a specific weighting, such a significant difference reduced the purchasing power of officials serving in Munich in comparison with that of their colleagues serving in Bonn. </inglise>
<eesti> 1987. aasta l&otilde;pul oli elukallidus M&uuml;nchenis 8,3% k&otilde;rgem kui Bonnis (tolleaegses pealinnas) ning eraldi paranduskoefitsiendi puudumise t&otilde;ttu v&auml;hendas selline m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne erinevus M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ostuj&otilde;udu v&otilde;rreldes nende Bonnis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate kolleegide omaga. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, in view of the wide discrepancy found in this case, the obligation to establish a specific weighting could not depend on the number of officials and other servants of the Communities concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealusel juhul t&auml;heldatud suurt lahknevust silmas pidades ei tohiks eraldi paranduskoefitsiendi kehtestamise kohustus s&otilde;ltuda &uuml;henduste asjaomaste ametnike ja muude teenistujate arvust. </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas as a result of these considerations the Regulation in question must be declared void insofar as it omits to fix a specific weighting for Munich with effect from 1 January 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud kaalutlustel tuleb k&otilde;nealune m&auml;&auml;rus tunnistada kehtetuks, kuiv&otilde;rd sellega ei kehtestata M&uuml;ncheni jaoks 1. jaanuarist 1988 j&otilde;ustuvat eraldi paranduskoefitsienti." </eesti>
<inglise> ' ; </inglise>
<eesti> ; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the above Judgment should be acted on by fixing a specific weighting for Munich with effect from 1 January 1988 and updated from that date to 1 July 1991, </inglise>
<eesti> eespool kirjeldatud kohtuotsuse p&otilde;hjal tuleks kehtestada M&uuml;ncheni jaoks alates 1. jaanuarist 1988 kohaldatav eraldi paranduskoefitsient ning seda tuleks ajakohastada alates nimetatud kuup&auml;evast kuni 1. juulini 1991, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> With effect from 1 January 1988, the weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants serving in Munich shall be 107,8 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. jaanuarist 1988 kohaldatakse M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes paranduskoefitsienti 107,8%. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> With effect from 1 July 1988, the weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants serving in Munich shall be 108,3 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. juulist 1988 kohaldatakse M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes paranduskoefitsienti 108,3 %. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> With effect from 1 July 1989, the weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants serving in Munich shall be 107,3 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. juulist 1989 kohaldatakse M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes paranduskoefitsienti 107,3 %. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> With effect from 1 July 1990, the weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants serving in Munich shall be 103,3 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. juulist 1990 kohaldatakse M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes paranduskoefitsienti 103,3 %. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> With effect from 1 July 1991, the weighting applicable to the remuneration of officials and other servants serving in Munich shall be 102,8 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. juulist 1991 kohaldatakse M&uuml;nchenis t&ouml;&ouml;tavate ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasude suhtes paranduskoefitsienti 102,8 %. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
